<paragraph id="1019E25DA526FFFBFF07FC9EFCEE737A" blockId="14.[136,817,806,833]" box="[136,817,806,833]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
<heading id="4B515531A526FFFBFF07FC9EFCEE737A" bold="true" box="[136,817,806,833]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" reason="1">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF07FC9EFCEE737A" bold="true" box="[136,817,806,833]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
Transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE9AFC9EFD97737A" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[277,584,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE9AFC9EFD97737A" bold="true" box="[277,584,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
back to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD21FC9EFCEE737A" box="[686,817,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD21FC9EFCEE737A" bold="true" box="[686,817,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BCB1D6A526FFFBFF07FCD6FC5877FB" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" type="description">
<paragraph id="1019E25DA526FFFBFF07FCD6FE75745A" blockId="14.[136,1452,878,1985]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE89FCD6FE4A73B3" box="[262,405,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE89FCD6FE4A73B3" box="[262,405,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFDF4FCD6FBED73B3" author="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G." box="[635,1074,878,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="738 - 757" refId="ref12746" refString="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G. (2012) Cat's eyes and popcorn flowers: Phylogenetic systematics of the genus Cryptantha s. l. (Boraginaceae). Systematic Botany 37: 738 - 757. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364412 X 648706" type="journal article" year="2012">Hasenstab-Lehman &amp; Simpson (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, who added to the two originally described species of the genus— 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD8CFC2BFCAF7397" authority="Brand (1925: 249)" authorityName="Brand" authorityPageNumber="249" authorityYear="1925" box="[515,880,914,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD8CFC2BFD4E7397" box="[515,657,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. inaequata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFD14FC2AFCAF7397" author="Brand, A." box="[667,880,914,941]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="249 - 254" refId="ref12067" refString="Brand, A. (1925) Drei neue Gattungen der Cryptantheae. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 21: 249 - 254." type="journal article" year="1925">Brand (1925: 249)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFC23FC2BFACB7396" authority="Brand (1925: 249)" authorityName="Brand" authorityPageNumber="249" authorityYear="1925" box="[940,1300,914,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFC23FC2BFBE87397" box="[940,1079,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. racemosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFBCFFC2AFACB7396" author="Brand, A." box="[1088,1300,914,941]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="249 - 254" refId="ref12067" refString="Brand, A. (1925) Drei neue Gattungen der Cryptantheae. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 21: 249 - 254." type="journal article" year="1925">Brand (1925: 249)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
—by making 11 new combinations, one of these 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD97FC0EFC9D73EB" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[536,834,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD97FC0EFC9D73EB" box="[536,834,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, of these 13 species in the genus, only eight had been sequenced and verified from molecular phylogenetic evidence to be part of the same clade, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFA93FC62FEC37423" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFA93FC62FEC37423" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not among these. The basis for transferring this species to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFC39FC46FB9A7423" box="[950,1093,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFC39FC46FB9A7423" box="[950,1093,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was morphology of the nutlets, those of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF66FB9BFE487407" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[233,407,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF66FB9BFE487407" box="[233,407,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being heteromorphic with whitish tubercles (in the consimilar nutlets), similar to many other members of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE9BFBFEFE7C745B" box="[276,419,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE9BFBFEFE7C745B" box="[276,419,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA526FFFBFF32FBD2FE5E75BA" blockId="14.[136,1452,878,1985]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
The subsequent molecular phylogenetic study of 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFD64FBD2FC3174BF" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Guilliams, C. M. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L." box="[747,1006,1130,1157]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="1406 - 1420" refId="ref14215" refString="Simpson, M. G., Guilliams, C. M., Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L. (2017 a) Phylogeny of the popcorn flowers: Use of genome skimming to evaluate monophyly and interrelationships in subtribe Amsinckiinae (Boraginaceae). Taxon 66: 1406 - 1420. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFCDAFBD3FC5774BF" box="[853,904,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">et al</emphasis>
. (2017a)
</bibRefCitation>
expanded the study of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFB77FBD2FA5874BF" box="[1272,1415,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFB77FBD2FA5874BF" box="[1272,1415,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by sequencing 11 of the 13 species, verifying that 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD00FB36FCC17493" box="[655,798,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD00FB36FCC17493" box="[655,798,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constitutes a well-supported clade separate from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF07FB0AFED774F7" box="[136,264,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF07FB0AFED774F7" box="[136,264,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These authors also noted additional species of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFCB1FB0AFC6174F7" box="[830,958,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFCB1FB0AFC6174F7" box="[830,958,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grouping with 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFBFAFB0AFADB74F7" box="[1141,1284,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFBFAFB0AFADB74F7" box="[1141,1284,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, four of these later transferred to the latter genus (
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFD96FB6EFCDE74CB" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K." box="[537,769,1238,1265]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="279 - 289" refId="ref14356" refString="Simpson, M. G., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. (2019) Transfer of four species of Cryptantha to the genus Johnstonella (Boraginaceae). Phytotaxa 425: 279 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 425.5.3" type="journal article" year="2019">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD0AFB6FFD6974CB" box="[645,694,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). However, two species that had been placed in 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFA93FB6EFA7474CB" box="[1308,1451,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFA93FB6EFA7474CB" box="[1308,1451,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originally by 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFE92FB42FD15752F" author="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G." box="[285,714,1274,1300]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="738 - 757" refId="ref12746" refString="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G. (2012) Cat's eyes and popcorn flowers: Phylogenetic systematics of the genus Cryptantha s. l. (Boraginaceae). Systematic Botany 37: 738 - 757. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364412 X 648706" type="journal article" year="2012">Hasenstab-Lehman &amp; Simpson (2012)</bibRefCitation>
based on morphology, but not sequenced by them, did not fall into the 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF3FFAA6FEE07503" box="[176,319,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF3FFAA6FEE07503" box="[176,319,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade in the later study, these being 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD43FAA7FCA67503" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[716,889,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD43FAA7FCA67503" box="[716,889,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which grouped with 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFBE6FAA6FA8A7503" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1129,1365,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFBE6FAA6FA8A7503" box="[1129,1365,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of their 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF07FAFBFF217567" box="[136,254,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade (see below) and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD89FAFBFB297566" authority="(Gray 1883: 90) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityPageNumber="90" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[518,1270,1346,1373]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micromeres">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD89FAFBFD7B7567" box="[518,676,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. micromeres</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFD3BFAFAFC847567" author="Gray, A." box="[692,859,1346,1372]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref12456" refString="Gray, A. (1883) Contributions to North American botany. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 19: 1 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25138721" type="journal article" year="1883">Gray 1883: 90</bibRefCitation>
) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, which grouped within 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF58FADEFE8875BB" box="[215,343,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF58FADEFE8875BB" box="[215,343,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A526FFFBFED2FADFFE5E75BA" box="[349,385,1383,1409]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA526FFFBFF32FA32FE82776F" blockId="14.[136,1452,878,1985]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE0AFA32FD71759F" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[389,686,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE0AFA32FD71759F" box="[389,686,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does resemble other members of that genus in having nutlets that are heteromorphic (a condition found in a total of eight species of the genus, including 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFBB3FA17FB3475F3" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1084,1259,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFBB3FA17FB3475F3" box="[1084,1259,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in having a white-minutely tuberculate nutlet sculpturing, although the latter feature is restricted to the three smaller, consimilar nutlets. However, we point out that the consimilar nutlets of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFCDCFA4FFBDA762B" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[851,1029,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFCDCFA4FFBDA762B" box="[851,1029,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also rather similar in shape and sculpturing to the “rough” nutlets (when present) of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD58F9A2FC1A760F" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[727,965,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD58F9A2FC1A760F" box="[727,965,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; e.g., compare 
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A526FFFBFBFCF9A2FB18760F" box="[1139,1223,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[239,1349,187,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-19@1.[239,1349,187,1709]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exemplars of three varieties of Cryptantha maritima. A–C.Cryptantha m. var. maritima.A. Image of original material: Greene s.n., 26 Apr 1885, Mexico, Baja California, Guadalupe Island (UC193934). Note bracts and hispid vestiture. B. Field image, showing bracts and small corollas; photograph by Jon Rebman, 2 April 2008, Mexico, Baja California Sur, Laguna San Ignacio. C. Nutlets of fruit, one larger smooth (left) and one smaller tuberculate (right), from Simpson 2933 (SDSU19298). D, E. Cryptantha m. var. cedrosensis. D. Field image, showing larger corolla of this variety; photograph by Jon Rebman, 31 March 2015, Mexico, Baja California, Cedros Island. E. Fruiting calyx with four nutlets dissected out, these heteromorphic with one larger smooth and three smaller tuberculate; from Rebman 2446, 17 March 1994 (HCIB6234). F–H. Cryptantha m. var. pilosa. F. Field image, showing bracts, dense tufts of hirsute trichomes, and small corollas; photograph courtesy of Pablo Ruiz, United States, Pima County, Arizona, Saguaro National Park, iNaturalist observation 39812503. G, H. Images from C.V. Morton 2061, 19 March 1949 (SD113111). G. Close-up of flowers and fruits, showing calyces with dense tufts of whitish, ascending hirsute trichomes, characteristic of this variety. H. Solitary nutlet of fruit, this smooth." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426138/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
or 4C with 
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A526FFFBFADFF9A2FA78760F" box="[1360,1447,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[209,1386,197,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[201,1386,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cryptantha echinosepala [Johnstonella e.] fruit of exemplar, León 3465, 15 March 2003 (SD153719). A. Fruit with four heteromorphic nutlets removed.Note relatively small, persistent corolla. B. Close-up of large “odd” nutlet, in dorsal (left), ventral (middle), and side (right) views. Note tuberculate-spinulose sculpturing. C. Close-up of one of the small “consimilar” nutlets, in dorsal (left), ventral (middle), and side (right) views. Note tuberculate sculpturing, lacking spinules." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426154/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFEAAF987FE097663" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[293,470,1598,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFEAAF987FE097663" box="[293,470,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFD4EF987FC937663" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[705,844,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFD4EF987FC937663" box="[705,844,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including our newly named 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFB2DF987FA7B7663" authorityName="Rebman &amp; M. G. Simpson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1186,1444,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="vizcainensis">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFB2DF987FB067663" box="[1186,1241,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">C. m</emphasis>
. var. 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFA92F987FA7B7663" box="[1309,1444,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">vizcainensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF70F9DBFEB77647" authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[255,360,1634,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF70F9DBFEB77647" box="[255,360,1634,1661]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">C. pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the odd nutlet in the “axial” position, i.e., closest to the inflorescence axis (
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFB70F9DAFA787646" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[1279,1447,1634,1661]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref13012" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1925) Studies in the Boraginaceae IV. The North American species of Cryptantha. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 74: 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1925">Johnston 1925</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFF07F93EFF1C769B" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[136,195,1670,1696]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="73 - 83" refId="ref13085" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1928) Studies in the Boraginaceae - VII. 2. Notes on various Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 81: 73 - 83." type="journal article" year="1928">1928</bibRefCitation>
, current study). In contrast, all of the other heteromorphic species of 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFC45F93EFBAA769A" box="[970,1141,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFC45F93EFB86769B" box="[970,1113,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Johnstonella</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFBFAF93FFD8976FE" authority="(Johnston 1924: 1143) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Johnston" baseAuthorityPageNumber="1143" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelica">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFBFAF93FFB2F769B" box="[1141,1264,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. angelica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFB70F93EFF1F76FF" author="Johnston, I. M." pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="951 - 1218" refId="ref12967" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1924) Expedition of the California Academy of Sciences to the Gulf of California in 1921: The botany (the vascular plants). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 12: 951 - 1218." type="journal article" year="1924">Johnston 1924: 1143</bibRefCitation>
) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFDEDF913FA7876FE" authority="(Torrey 1857: 363) Hasenstab &amp; M. G. Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; M. G. Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Torrey" baseAuthorityPageNumber="363" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[610,1447,1706,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFDEDF913FCDD76FF" box="[610,770,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. angustifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFC9FF912FC0976FE" author="Torrey, J." box="[784,982,1706,1733]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" refId="ref14514" refString="Torrey, J. (1857) Appendix. Article VII. Descriptions of plants collected along the route, by W. P. Blake, and at the mouth of the Gila. In: Williamson, R. S. (Ed.) Report of Explorations in California for Railroad Routes to Connect with the Routes Near the 35 th and 32 d Parallels of North Latitude 5. Beverley Tucker, Washington D. C., 363 pp." type="book" year="1857">Torrey 1857: 363</bibRefCitation>
) Hasenstab &amp; M.G.Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF07F977FC4176D2" authority="(Philippi 1891: 57) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityPageNumber="57" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[136,926,1742,1769]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diplotricha">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF07F977FEFE76D3" box="[136,289,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. diplotricha</emphasis>
(Philippi 1891: 57) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFC23F977FE437736" authority="(Johnston 1939: 388) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Johnston" baseAuthorityPageNumber="388" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fastigiata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFC23F977FBEC76D3" box="[940,1075,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. fastigiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFBCCF976FAF976D3" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[1091,1318,1742,1768]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="375 - 402" refId="ref13122" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1939) Studies in the Boraginaceae, XIII: New or otherwise noteworthy species, chiefly from western United States. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 20: 375 - 402. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21105" type="journal article" year="1939">Johnston 1939: 388</bibRefCitation>
) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE24F94BFDE77737" authorityName="Brand" authorityYear="1925" box="[427,568,1779,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE24F94BFDE77737" box="[427,568,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. inaequata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFDC6F94BFA887736" authority="(Philippi 1860: 39) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityPageNumber="754" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityPageNumber="39" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[585,1367,1778,1805]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parviflora">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFDC6F94BFD077737" box="[585,728,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. parviflora</emphasis>
(Philippi 1860: 39) Hasenstab &amp; Simpson (2012: 754)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFA17F94BFF2A770B" authorityName="Brand" authorityYear="1925" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFA17F94BFF2A770B" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">J. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—have the odd nutlet positioned in the abaxial position, i.e. away from the inflorescence axis (
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFAC9F8AEFF1C776E" author="Johnston, I. M." pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref13012" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1925) Studies in the Boraginaceae IV. The North American species of Cryptantha. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 74: 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1925">Johnston 1925</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFF41F882FED6776F" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[206,265,1850,1876]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref13048" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1927) Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1927">1927</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA526FFFBFE9BF882FE8F776F" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[276,336,1850,1876]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" pagination="375 - 402" refId="ref13122" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1939) Studies in the Boraginaceae, XIII: New or otherwise noteworthy species, chiefly from western United States. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 20: 375 - 402. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21105" type="journal article" year="1939">1939</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA526FFFBFF32F8E6FC5877FB" blockId="14.[136,1452,878,1985]" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">
The most recent molecular phylogenetic analysis, along with our observations based on morphology (including nutlet position), argue that 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFE34F83AFD3877A7" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Macbride" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[443,743,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFE34F83AFD3877A7" box="[443,743,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Johnstonella echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be transferred back to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFB3AF83AFAEA77A7" box="[1205,1333,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFB3AF83AFAEA77A7" box="[1205,1333,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, we accept 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA526FFFBFF58F81EFE2E77FB" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[215,497,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA526FFFBFF58F81EFE2E77FB" box="[215,497,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="199">Cryptantha echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the correct name for this species.
</paragraph>
